Description: Disable PIE to fix segfault in 32-bit assembly trampoline
 code.asm uses absolute addresses for C globals (saveFS, saveGS, saveESP,
 jumptramp, etc.) via NASM EXTERN declarations compiled with -f elf32.
 These absolute references are incompatible with Position Independent
 Executables (PIE), which Ubuntu enables by default. When the binary is
 loaded as PIE, the runtime relocations are not applied correctly to the
 32-bit ELF object, causing a SIGSEGV in the far-call trampoline during
 demo startup.
 .
 Add -fno-pie to CFLAGS and -no-pie to LDFLAGS to produce a non-PIE ELF
 executable, restoring the expected absolute addressing for code.asm.
